  "title": "Nursing Aide #SGUnitedJobs",
  "description": "<p><u>Clinical Care</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assists the registered nurses in the delivery of nursing care to the residents in the Home.</li>\n  <li>Assists all nursing procedures which include administration of medications, wound dressing and meal feeding.</li>\n  <li>Ensures the comfort and good personal hygiene of the residents under her/his care, e.g. bed bath/shower bath, changing of clothes and bed sheets and tidiness of the room.</li>\n  <li>Helps to maintain a clean, safe and neat environment for the residents in the nursing home.</li>\n  <li>Accompanies residents to the hospital/polyclinic for follow-up appointments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Training and Development</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Attend upgrading programs to keep abreast with clinical knowledge and to develop work-required skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Administration</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assists in the admission and orientation of new residents</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ensure all documentation of residents’ case is maintained appropriately.</p>\n<p><u>Locally Trained</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>GCE N Level</li>\n  <li>Attained Training in either one of the courses:<br>\nWSQ Higher Certificate / Advanced Certificate / in Healthcare Support (Nursing Care)<br>\nInstitute of Technical Education (ITE) Approved Training Centre (ATC) Healthcare (Home Care) Programme</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Successful applicants without the qualifications will be sent for Certificate in Community Care (Community Care Traineeship Programme) with all courses funded by the employer.</p>",
